<section class="pmfSeasonWrap pmfSeasonOutlinePanel">
<section class="pmfSeasonWrap pmfSeasonOutlinePanel pmf2024">
<div class="row">
<div class="col panel01">
<h1>PMF 2024</h1>
<p><strong>July 10 - July 30</strong><br>Highlights</p>
</div>
<div class="col panel02">
<a href="#panel02" class="panelTrg nopscr">
<span class="inner">
After taking the world stage, <br>a triumphant return to PMF
</span>
</a>
<div class="panelContents noSchedule" id="panel02">
<p class="panelTitle panelClose">PMF 2024<br>
<small>July 12 - July 30 Highlights</small></p>
<img src="../../img/2024/bg_panel_02_l.webp" class="bg">
<img src="../../img/2017/bg_panel.png" class="bg spNone">
<div class="main">
<p class="catch">After taking the world stage, a triumphant return to PMF</p>
<h2 class="mainTitle">PMF Orchestra [Program A]</h2>
<div class="inner">
<p class="mb20">Once a member of the PMF Academy, Germany-based conductor Elias Grandy has gone on to flourish on the world stage, and in April 2025 he will take on the role of Chief Conductor of the Sapporo Symphony Orchestra. But first, in 2024 he makes his triumphant return to PMF!</p>
<p class="mb20">Grandy marks his return with a captivating lineup of masterworks, balancing delicate timbres with powerful grandiosity, each written early in their respective composers’ oeuvres. He will lead the PMF Orchestra in Strauss’ <i>Don Juan</i>, Debussy’s <i>Prélude à l'après-midi d'un faune</i>, and Stravinsky’s Firebird Suite, and the virtuosic mastery of soloist Clara-Jumi Kang will be on full display in Prokofiev's Violin Concerto No. 1!</p>
<p class="fsSmall textRight">Text: Masahide Hayashi</p>
</div>
<div class="inner">
<h3 class="title">Date</h3>
<table class="date">
<tr>
<td><a href="https://www.pmf.or.jp/en/schedule/orchestra/2024-tomakomai.html" target="_blank">July 13 (Sat)</a></td>
<td class="access">PMF Orchestra Concert in Tomakomai <br class="pc">(Tomakomai Shimin Kaikan)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="https://www.pmf.or.jp/en/schedule/orchestra/2024-pmfo.html" target="_blank">July 14 (Sun)</a></td>
<td class="access">PMF Orchestra Concert <br class="pc">(Sapporo Concert Hall <i>Kitara</i>)</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
<div class="inner">
<h3 class="title">Artists</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.pmf.or.jp/en/artist/conductor/2024-C01.html" target="_blank">Elias Grandy, <i>conductor</i></a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.pmf.or.jp/en/artist/program_a/2024-A01.html" target="_blank">Clara-Jumi Kang, <i>violin</i>*</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.pmf.or.jp/en/artist/pmfe/2024-pmfe.html" target="_blank">PMF EUROPE (PMF VIENNA / PMF BERLIN)</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.pmf.or.jp/en/artist/pmfo/2024-pmfo.html" target="_blank">PMF Orchestra</a></p>
</div>
<div class="inner">
<h3 class="title">Program</h3>
<p>R. Strauss: Don Juan, Op. 20</p>
<p>Prokofiev: Violin Concerto No. 1 in D major, Op. 19*</p>
<p>Debussy: Prélude à l'après-midi d'un faune</p>
<p>Stravinsky: Firebird Suite (1919)</p>
</div>
<div class="column">
<figure class="photo">
<img src="../../img/2024/photo_contents_panel_02a.webp" width="200" height="200" alt="Elias Grandy">
<figcaption>Elias Grandy<br>&copy;Shervin Lainez</figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="photo">
<img src="../../img/2024/photo_contents_panel_02b.webp" width="200" height="200" alt="Clara-Jumi Kang">
<figcaption>Clara-Jumi Kang<br>&copy;Marco Borggreve</figcaption>
